title: Dentists Registration (Amendment) Bill gazetted
content_text:
p>The Dentists Registration (Amendment) Bill 2005 which seeks to enhance 
regulation of dental specialist practice by setting up a statute-based 
specialist register is gazetted today (June 30).  The current Dentists Registration Ordinance does not provide for the granting of 
specialist titles to registered dentists. Registered dentists are now granted 
the right to use specialist titles by the Hong Kong Dental Council through 
administrative arrangements. An administrative list is maintained by the Hong

administrative arrangements. An administrative list is maintained by the Hong 
Kong Dental Council.  A spokesman for the Health, Welfare and Food Bureau said the bill proposed to 
add new provisions to set up the Specialist Register, to specify the detailed 
procedures to include or remove a dentist's name in or from the register, as 
well as to impose criminal sanction against unauthorised use of specialist 
titles.  The bill proposes to subject people who use specialist titles without 
authorisation to a fine of $100,000 and imprisonment for three years on

authorisation to a fine of $100,000 and imprisonment for three years on 
conviction.  "The proposed amendments serve to better inform the public and enhance public 
confidence on the practice of dental specialists. The criminal sanction against 
unauthorised use of specialist titles will enhance the protection of public 
health," the spokesman said.  The establishment of specialist register will facilitate further advancement of 
dental specialist practice in Hong Kong. An Education and Accreditation 
Committee will be set up under the Dental Council to handle matters relating to

Committee will be set up under the Dental Council to handle matters relating to 
the Specialist Register and specialists.  Subject to the passage of the bill, those registered dentists who are on the 
administrative list will automatically be included in the Specialist Register.
 The Administration has consulted major stakeholder groups of the dentistry 
profession including the Hong Kong Dental Council and the Hong Kong Dental 
Association. They are supportive of the proposed amendments.
